Dlamini-Zuma says she's pleased Ghanaians exercised their democratic rights and has also applauded the country's electoral commission. JOHANNESBURG - African Union (AU) commission chair Nkosasana Dlamini-Zuma has congratulated Ghana's president elect Nana Akufo-Addo after general elections in his country earlier this month. The AU has also commended the incumbent President John Mahama for his service to the nation and for gracefully accepting the election results. Dlamini-Zuma says she's pleased Ghanaians exercised their democratic rights and has also applauded the country's electoral commission for managing the highly-contested polls, which were marked by tensions and anxiety.(Edited by Neo Koza)